<span id="freeTextContainer11710727848535643821">Great writing, but I couldn&apos;t give the book 5 stars because I found it so depressing and gloomy. The themes are in the title, but I guess I had hoped for at least one slightly hopeful or redeeming moment. I did not find them in this book. However, I have to acknowledge that Quiroga is definitely a master of the short story. For that I give it 4 stars, but I doubt I would re-read this except maybe a story or two on Halloween. I would say you definitely need a high intermediate or advanced level t</span>
  <span id="freeText11710727848535643821" style="display:none">Great writing, but I couldn't give the book 5 stars because I found it so depressing and gloomy. The themes are in the title, but I guess I had hoped for at least one slightly hopeful or redeeming moment. I did not find them in this book. However, I have to acknowledge that Quiroga is definitely a master of the short story. For that I give it 4 stars, but I doubt I would re-read this except maybe a story or two on Halloween. I would say you definitely need a high intermediate or advanced level to read in Spanish.</span>
