        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2068556485?book_show_action=true">Jul 30, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Marina Oppenheimer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Marina Oppenheimer" href="/user/show/44539424-marina-oppenheimer">Marina Oppenheimer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/11187594-cuentos-de-amor-de-locura-y-de-muerte">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2068556485" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4408207860553495268"><strong>Stories from Argentina</strong><br/><br/>Horacio Quiroga is a master story teller whose characters are minutely described and whose plots have a very appealing suspense. The stories take place in the Argentine country side where people live in close contact with nature. But nature in these stories is not a passive landscape. On the contrary, it can be sometimes diabolic. Recommended reading.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

