<div id="review_1564483352" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1564483352" />
    <a title="Bexen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1817926-bexen"><img alt="Bexen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1378551650p2/1817926.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1564483352?book_show_action=true">Feb 29, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bexen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bexen" href="/user/show/1817926-bexen">Bexen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1817926-bexen?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1564483352" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6810868033421867450">“Cuando Anaconda, en complicidad con los elementos nativos del trópico, meditó y planeó la reconquista del río, acababa de cumplir treinta años. Era entonces una joven serpiente de diez metros, en la plenitud de su vigor”.<br/><br/>Quiroga, Latin-American master of the short story, is also a master of the short sentence, the kind that can take you away in one breath and make you dream of stories untold and magical worlds never seen before. These stories are full of this kind of sentences and that is why o</span>
  <span id="freeText6810868033421867450" style="display:none">“Cuando Anaconda, en complicidad con los elementos nativos del trópico, meditó y planeó la reconquista del río, acababa de cumplir treinta años. Era entonces una joven serpiente de diez metros, en la plenitud de su vigor”.<br /><br />Quiroga, Latin-American master of the short story, is also a master of the short sentence, the kind that can take you away in one breath and make you dream of stories untold and magical worlds never seen before. These stories are full of this kind of sentences and that is why one can enjoy them so much, even if the endings are never joyful. Everything must always end in a tragedy. These are tales of death and insanity and love only when it takes to the first or the second. The tales from “Exiles” are by far the most accomplished and complex. They all take place in the same world and some of them almost at the same time, reinforcing the unavoidable immersion in Quiroga’s magical jungle world.<br /><br />I really enjoyed reading these tales from my childhood again and reading them in Spanish. They are all violently beautiful, powerful and terrible, like life itself.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6810868033421867450" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


