              <span id="reviewTextContainer16948378" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer436982836569436045">I really loved this book. I really like all this author works.<br/>I like the way he develops the plot slowly coming to a, sometimes abrupt, and original ending. The themes can be consider a little depressing, but I think they touch things that are common to everyone. Also one of the thing I really like is how he creates an implied context that give the story a wide background to be discover.<br/>My favorite story is <i>&quot;El Almohandon de Plumas&quot; (The Feather Pillow)</i> I rad it when I was very little and I was </span>
  <span id="freeText436982836569436045" style="display:none">I really loved this book. I really like all this author works.<br />I like the way he develops the plot slowly coming to a, sometimes abrupt, and original ending. The themes can be consider a little depressing, but I think they touch things that are common to everyone. Also one of the thing I really like is how he creates an implied context that give the story a wide background to be discover.<br />My favorite story is <i>"El Almohandon de Plumas" (The Feather Pillow)</i> I rad it when I was very little and I was really amazed. An interesting tip is that after it was released many people were so freaked out that they trough away their pillows... ^_^</span>
